pan><hr size=1> /em rant on.<br>
<br>
Why is it that everyone believes that AC is god and they try to do everything in their power to max their AC?<br>
<br>
I can not count how many times I have seen people post stupid math equations trying to figure out stats/damage/delay/etc..... Doesn't anyone every just play the damn game for fun?!?!<br>
<br>
I apologize for ranting, but I am a roleplayer that plays a &quot;roleplaying game&quot; and I enjoy the game for what it is. I DO care about stats, but I try to balance stats with appearance. If have 180 strength, but run around looking like a combo of ringmail/steel/crafted/leather....WHY!?!?!<br>
<br>
I refuse to wear full crafted. I could afford it easily, but I do not want to wear it because I think it looks dumb. I have yet to go through a day of EQ and not have someone say &quot;Why not go for crafted, the stats are alot better than your charred armor.&quot;<br>
<br>
I feel sorry for anyone that goes straight for stats and does not care about anything else, they truly are the kind of people that break games down into programming and equations and curse the fun out of a game.<br>
<br>
/em rant off.<br>
<br>
Sorry about that. As for all of you that agree with me and care about stats but still go for appearance and enjoy roleplaying. BTW, I do wear a couple pieces of crafted, but I do so only for appearance. (would never wear full set though)<br>
<br>
Ignore this post if you like, I just wanted to vent some steam after getting harassed each and everyday by powergamers. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/bbrellserilis.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=tembdaraangelknight>Tembdara AngelKnight</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(7/19/00 10:44:30 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AC is not god.</span><hr size=1> I wish I had a current Screen shot of ne to put here. I wear a mix mash of Armors, that I look like I came from a Good Will Store <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
My Best Stat is 142 STR<br>
<br>
Mainly because I like lookin good and Different<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/usoulstomper.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Soulstomper</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(7/19/00 10:48:20 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AC is not god.</span><hr size=1> That is cool to do that, you want to look like that. I just don't like people who wear stuff just for stats, not caring about anything else. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/udyninvifargent.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dynin Vifargent</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(7/19/00 11:08:47 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AC is not god.</span><hr size=1> look &gt; AC<br>
oh and i'm a MR/dex freak too <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/unillon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nillon</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>GD RPers</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(7/20/00 3:45:24 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.home.net/soj/itsme.jpg height=188 width=115></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AC is not god.</span><hr size=1> Bring on the ac, honestly your attitude will prevent you from getting groups around level 25 or so and up. <p>Nillon, level 55 Myrmidon, Brell Serilis</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/ulythe.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lythe</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_bluespot.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(7/20/00 5:43:30 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AC is not god.</span><hr size=1> Actually Nillon, I am 32nd and still wear my Freeport Militia tunic when I feel like being &quot;red&quot;.  No one minds and I assure you that with my strength, dex and agility..no one cares.  As to the &quot;attitude&quot; you refer to.  Everyone should play their character as they wish.  Those that have issues with that usually find themselves excluded from groups, rather than the other way around. <p>Lythe Shadowhand <BR>
Rogue of her 32nd Shadow  <BR>
Diplomat of the Order of Elder Dragons <BR>

If you call me Thief again, I shall be forced to remove your tongue!  If you call me a lady, I'll remove more than that!</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/urykilth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rykilth</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(7/20/00 6:46:04 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.cpl.net/~kurtds/pic/ryk.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AC is not god.</span><hr size=1> I still like wearing my Valorium over the 2 pieces of Deepwater Armor I have....some of the stats to me aren't worth the 4 raw AC points I'll gain.  (Only time I'll switch to this, is during BIG fights, or when I'm the puller / only tank)<br>
<br>
for instance:  I'm a half elf, I have low wisdom, so I lose just over a half of bubble of mana just by replacing my Valorium Helmet for a Deepwater Helm.  (not to metion 13MR.  I'm a Paladin, not a warrior, no natural bonus to Magic Resist <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ) As a Hybrid, I've gotta concentrate on several other attributes.<br>
<br>
<br>
(Not to mention Half elves look damn good in matching armor)  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <p>--------------------------------<br>
Rykilth Spiritblade<BR>
Holy Knight of Mithaniel Marr<BR>
Brell Serilis Server<BR>
Officer of the Legion of Heroes
</p><i>Edited by <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/urykilth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rykilth</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10> at: 7/20/00 5:47:03 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/bbrellserilis.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=copeland>Copeland</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(7/20/00 6:46:35 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AC is not god.</span><hr size=1> Why do you give a rat's a** about what other people find fun or like to do?  Who says that they aren't playing the game for fun if they pay attention to stats or equations or formulas?  If they like to pay attention to stats, how does it affect your ability to enjoy your 'roleplaying' game in the slightest?  So what if someone makes a suggestion?--just tell them you like what you're wearing; they're not going to make you change.<br>
<br>
In fact, someone coming up to you and saying, &quot;Hey, if you want to be a better fighter, you might want to change to XXX armor&quot; is EXACTLY what would happen in a real world scenario and so is actually <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>better</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> roleplaying than the concept of some professional fighter choosing inferior gear for its looks instead of its protection. <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>   &quot;Ummm, yes, Captain, I know we're about to assault the enemy position.  But this black turtleneck looks so much cooler than my flak jacket that I'd wear it, instead!&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
I don't agree with Nillon...I doubt choosing one type of armor over another will prevent you from getting into groups.  The player's attitude and reputation are, by far, the most important factors in that regard.  However, sounds to me like you want to have the privilege of doing the things that you find fun in the game...but refuse to grant that privilege to others, instead demanding that they play it your way and only enjoy the things you do.  If they do otherwise, they are powergamers and ruining it for everyone?...get over yourself.<br>
<br>
If you want to wear armor for its appearance, that's perfectly fine.  If others want to select armor based upon its defensive ability, that's perfectly fine, too. <p><font color=8bb4d2 face="Garamond"><b>- Cope -</b></font></p><i>Edited by <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/bbrellserilis.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=copeland>Copeland</A> at: 7/20/00 6:07:03 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/usoulstomper.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Soulstomper</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(7/20/00 9:39:11 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AC is not god.</span><hr size=1> Copeland, perhaps you misunderstood me. If you wish to wear armor just for the stats and equations of damage/delay fine, go right ahead. I am not trying to suggest that you do so, I just am trying to say that I get bible-thumped by the 'AC is god' street-preachers everywhere I go. I am merely stating my opinion and telling people like that to please LEAVE ME BE. Just like you said I play the game my way and you play it your way, I just am sick of getting told to change my items to the &quot;median&quot; of Norrathian society.<br>
<br>
Also, to you others that think I will have trouble getting a group: That is false. It IS your reputation that gets you in a group, not what equipment you have. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/uthoricofbrell.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Thoric of Brell</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(7/20/00 10:09:42 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AC is not god.</span><hr size=1> Two points regarding reputation. It only gets you a group if the people there know you. With the massive influx of new level 50'ish people I've been seeing, I can go into places like Karnor's and not recognize more than 3 people in the zone. And I know a lot of people. <br>
<br>
Second, if everyone is bugging you about your armor, your reputation may become.. &quot;That guy who wears the crummy armor&quot;. =D Anyway, Nillon has one point, which is that part of your rep is how you perform, and how you are equipped is an element of that. Is it the only one? Nope. But its not something that has no effect, as you'd apparently like to think. <br>
<br>
Thoric Frosthammer<br>
Silent Redemption <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/uevanar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Evanar</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(7/20/00 2:09:02 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/dbzvegetastyle/images/gohanpower.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AC is not god.</span><hr size=1> Somedays I feel like finding just all the black armor I can and just using piercers to let the world know I'm a rogue.  But then I feel like not being a mana sponge and using high AC stuff and using slashers and perhaps blunt.  So, I'm a moody character.  I guess I'm roleplaying. <p>Xavilan Swiftedge, 31st Level Scout of Tunare<BR>Evanar Avelinkin, 20th Level Dark Elf Cleric<BR>Brell Serilis (Vigilant Eyes of Norrath)</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/udyninvifargent.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dynin Vifargent</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(7/20/00 3:46:55 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AC is not god.</span><hr size=1> nillon : take a deep breathe and calm down<br>
<br>
even if i like to go for AC most of the time i'm switching it for resist gear as soon as i meet a caster and i'm a real dex freak with a procing weapon ( i carry 4 bags full of extra gear on me all the time and i switch my gear all the time )<br>
<br>
i know other warriors fucusing on stats and they are still great warriors.. look at tumagok for example he's going for straight strengh and you can trust me he's doing a freaking lot of damage with a very high strengh..<br>
of course just 10 more strengh wouldnt make a big difference.. but 10 AC wouldnt do anything<br>
last time i checked though he was at 230 str or something like that... and with a strengh that high his damage is pretty heavy<br>
<br>
and anyway even if it was less effective, the person playing the warrior still matters a lot more than a higher AC or any other stat <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/uthoricofbrell.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Thoric of Brell</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(7/20/00 4:57:20 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AC is not god.</span><hr size=1> Dynin-it depends on the tradeoff you are making in my opinion. AC seems to really make a big difference about every 100 points. I.e. if that big str difference is only knocking you from 890 to 870 no biggie. But if its keeping you under 900 when you could be over, I'd stick to AC. I started taking a lot less damage back when I hit 800, and i noticed a lesser but noticable improvement at 900. Anyway, you are correct in saying that a smart warrior is better than a stupid one whatever his armor class, but I still think sometimes it's worth sacrficing a look in the interest of performance.<br>
<br>
Thoric Frosthammer<br>
Silent Redemption <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/bbrellserilis.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=tembdaraangelknight>Tembdara AngelKnight</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(7/20/00 9:26:02 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AC is not god.</span><hr size=1> Hehe I look like a Calico Cat. but I got to admit having 890AC with my Prime Stats all above 120 is nice. But then again I've been trying to do a balancing act with everything. I find I do a Pretty damn good job as a tank even without a haste Item and knowing how to us4e what I got is a Plus <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/usoulstomper.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Soulstomper</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(7/21/00 10:59:07 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AC is not god.</span><hr size=1> Just because you have good items does not make your performance perfect. I was grouped with a twinked paladin with a Jade Reaver, and a combo of Ro and Mithril armor. He wasnted to pull (was in MM) and every time he did pull a train of 6+ things came barreling in. Then he rarely used his healing spells (except LoH which he used on himself), would fight things out of the bard Lull song range and made it hard on the rogue in our group to get a Backstab in. He had great items, but couldn't play his character very well. Just my little story. (= <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/uthoricofbrell.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Thoric of Brell</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(7/21/00 2:03:29 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AC is not god.</span><hr size=1> By the same logic, just because you are a reasonably good warrior, it doesn't mean that good equipment and AC can't make you better. It's all interdependant, which is all I have really been trying to say all along. It is equally foolish to assume that two warriors of equal skill will not be seperated by the quality of their equipment as it is to assume that two warriors with the same equipment will not be seperated by their skill. Guess my point is, people flame on Nillon for pointing out that equipment is an important factor if you want to push your abilities to the highest level they can be. <br>
<br>
Thoric Frosthammer <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/ugoatfrenesi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Goat Frenesi</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Goat Under Your Foot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(7/21/00 5:41:27 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/goatsghetto/kam-head.gif width=87 height=120></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AC is not god.</span><hr size=1> AC is not god...I AM GOD.<br>
