<br>
Actually, AC is not god.  Level is god.  Skill is demigod.  AC is pope, HP and resists are lesser nobles, stats are court jesters.<br>
<br>
I love having a high AC.  Getting hurt less is a good thing.  I spend less time on my butt, the healer spends less time on his or her butt.  In general it allows me to play more instead of resting.<br>
<br>
Style points are nice, too.  Honestly I will not proselytize if someone I know is playing the game their own way (at least as far as equipment).  Players who will not /assist or forget to snare, on the other hand, can take a hike.  This sort of think causes the game to absolutely not be much fun for me at higher levels.<br>
<br>
So anyway, play EQ however you want, just as long as you're not getting mr needlessly hurt or killed. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/ubrontothunderfoot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bronto Thunderfoot</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(7/22/00 9:19:49 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Hah hahah, Goat!!</span><hr size=1> I have to agree with Nillon and Thoric on this one.  Skill only goes so far. Equipment only goes so far.  The combination of the two determines how effective a player you are. I see some level 54+ tanks wearing Mith BPs, almost full quest armor and other level 35ish pieces.  I don't care how well you play your class...but by the mid-50's if you are still wearing that sort of equipment you are NOT an EFFECTIVE tank (notice i didnt say &quot;good&quot; just not effective).  You are not doing the damage you have the potential to do. You are taking ALOT more damage than you should. And these things hinder you from playing as skillfully as you would like.  If it's your job to taunt, and you're not doing alot of damage because your equipment isnt very good then you will not be able to taunt as well, no matter how good you are at getting a mob's attention through other means (pallys can with stun, but warriors, damage IS your taunt). And if you are taking alot of damage very quickly your healer is going to need to blow all of his/her mana on you, leaving him/her lom or oom for when a caster or a weaker class that is expected to take damage needs that heal.<br>
<br>
Yes, if you want to look cool, by all means wear that equip when you're in a safe camp (tearing up stuff in L Guk comes to mind) or when you're running around.  But when I'm in sebilis and the puller brings about 5 frogs and our enchanter is having trouble mezzing them...  when I look to my side in between swings during this frenzied fight, I dont want to see a warrior wearing black iron and rubicite getting his ass handed to him by some punk dar knight, I'd rather see a half-elf or ogre, or hell even gnome, standing tall and swinging furiously while the blows deflect off his indicolite and cobalt.<br>
<br>
And yes I know good armor is not easy to get...but if you have the time to level to 54+ by now than you certainly should have the time to raid the planes, or the money to buy some high-ac kunark class armor.<br>
<br>
I know this might sound kinda elitist to some, like I'm trying to insult people without the best equipment, please don't take it that way.  I'm just saying that equipment DOES matter, and CAN make you a better player.  And also remember the smaller the group, the more it matters.  In a 30+ person raid your own personal equipment might not make a big difference, but when half your group dies and 3 of you are left fighting for your lives in a close match with some baddies, every piece of equip you have on you comes into play.<br>
<br>
&quot;But Bronto this is a GAME&quot;, you'll say, &quot;we're playing it to have FUN not to worry about exp and efficiency!!&quot;<br>
And I have no problem with that...but when one death can cost you 8+ hours of play time, and advancement comes so slow (and yes advancement is alot of what makes this game fun, that's why so many people got bored at level 50) gettign exp efficiently and not dying help to make this game fun.  The same people who talk about how they just play the game for fun are often the ones who complain the loudest about how slowly they are gaining levels, or who are hurt the most when they die.<br>
<br>
And keep in mind, your equipment effects your entire group.  Never bothered getting more WIS gear? well maybe if you had you could've gotten off that extra heal before you went oom and saved the wizard's life...how many corpses have you seen at the zone line?  Or maybe if you had better ac it wouldnt have gotten interrupted.  <br>
<br>
These are just some things to ponder regarding equipment and how it effects the playing experience.  It does make a difference<br>
<br>
